PULL REQUEST UNDER REVIEW:
REPO: eclipse-wildwebdeveloper/wildwebdeveloper
PR #316: Add extended JSON schema support via JSON preference page
Changed files (12): org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/plugin.xml, org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/SchemaAssociation.java, org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/SchemaAssociationDialog.java, org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/SchemaAssociationsMessages.java, org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/SchemaAssociationsMessages.properties, org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/SchemaAssociationsPreferenceInitializer.java, org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/SchemaAssociationsPreferencePage.java, org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/json/JSonLanguageServer.java, org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/yaml/YAMLLanguageServer.java, org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/yaml/YAMLPreferenceInitializer.java, org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/yaml/YAMLPreferencePage.java, org.eclipse.wildwebdeveloper/src/org/eclipse/wildwebdeveloper/yaml/YAMLSchemaPreferencePage.java
Diff (+857/-288):
PR DESCRIPTION:
Thank you for your hint to implement the JSON schema associations via preference pages (see PR #166 ).
I added a new preference page to associate JSON schemata to file patterns. The user can now define the schema location either by adding a valid URL or a local file path.
Also, the existing schema associations are added as default entries (except for the schema 'typing.json', as mentioned in my initial PR comment).

I am looking forward to your opinion on this change.
Best regards!

